title: Amari DuBose runs for four TDs as Westside rallies past Parker
text:
Amari DuBose runs for four TDs as Westside rallies past Parker 
Sat, Oct 17, 2015 @ 12:29 am 
4-5A 
WESTSIDE 42 
PARKER 30 
Star of the game: After a slow start and trailing 13-0 after the first quarter, Westside QB Amari DuBose started to find the running lanes, rushing for 124 yards on 21 carries. DuBose outscored Parker after the first quarter, rushing for four scores as the Wolverines defeated Parker on homecoming. 
Turning point: Tied at 20 at halftime, the Braves got the opening possession of the second half and a field goal broke the tie. DuBose scored on the ensuing drive to put Westside (2-5, 1-2) ahead 28-23 after a two-point conversion. Parker QB Erik Hill was hit and fumbled on the next drive, giving DuBose a short field, and the senior QB ran for his third score, extending the lead to 36-23 over the Braves (3-4, 1-2). 
On defense: Shawnree Singleton picked off Parker freshman QB Cameron Sapp, who came in for the injured Hill in the third quarter. 
Fast facts: Isaac Ricks rushed for 107 yards and two TDs for Parker. … Reginald Garrett returned a kickoff 70 yards for a TD for the Braves. … Drevon Eason rushed for 68 yards and a score. 
They said it: “We came out and got down early and had to trust the game plan and execute with the athletes that we have and we did that once we found a rhythm,” — Westside coach Rodney DuBose. George Wahl The Times-Union
